'''Kumata Shrine''' (杭全神社, ''Kumata Jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in Hirano-miyamachi, Hirano-ku, Osaka. It was originally a {{ill|Kumano Gongen|ja|熊野権現|12=draft}} Shrine dedicated to the {{ill|Kumano Sansho Gongen|ja|熊野三所権現|12=draft}}. Its former {{ill|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|ja|近代社格制度|12=draft}} was Prefectural Shrine. It is worshipped as the clan shrine (ujigami) of the {{ill|Sakanoue clan|ja|坂上氏|12=draft}} and of {{ill|Hirano, Osaka|ja|平野郷|12=draft}}. The summer festival (Hirano Danjiri Festival) is held annually from July 11 to 14, restricting traffic on nearby {{ill|National Route 25|ja|国道25号|12=draft}}.

== History ==
{{ill|Jōgan|ja|貞観|12=draft}} 4 ({{ill|862|ja|862nd year|12=draft}}), {{ill|Sakanoue no Tamuramaro|ja|坂上田村麻呂|12=draft}}'s grandson {{ill|Sakanoue no Tōdō|ja|坂上当道|12=draft}} established the shrine to {{ill|Gozu Tennō|ja|牛頭天王|1=Gozu Tennō|1=Gozu Tennō|12=draft}} (Susanoo-no-Mikoto) which became the First Main Hall.

== Worshipped deities (Saijin) ==
{{see also|{{ill|Saijin|ja|祭神|12=draft}}}}
Main deities worshipped:
* First Main Hall - {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|ja|素盞嗚尊|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gozu Tennō|ja|牛頭天王|1=Gozu Tennō|1=Gozu Tennō|12=draft}})
* Second Main Hall - {{ill|Izanami-no-Mikoto|ja|伊弉册尊|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hayatama-no-Mikoto|ja|速玉男尊|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kotosaka-no-Mikoto|ja|事解男尊|12=draft}} ({{ill|Kumano Sansho Gongen|ja|熊野三所権現|12=draft}})
* Third Main Hall - {{ill|Izanagi-no-Mikoto|ja|伊弉諾尊|12=draft}} ({{ill|Kumano Shōjō Gongen|ja|熊野證誠権現|12=draft}})

